  "texts": [
    "For each voxel, we select the class with the highest predicted probability (the argmax rule), 4 and then compare the resulting labels to the ground truth.",
    "The accuracy is defined as the fraction of voxels that are correctly classified.",
    "We adopt the argmax criterion because the optimized thresholds presented in section 2.6 are derived from the validation phase and therefore cannot be applied during training.",
    "copra achieves validation accuracies around 85%, while vipr consistently exceeds 90%, demonstrating superior performance.",
    "In all cases, the training, validation, and test accuracies are closely aligned, which suggests that the models generalize well to unseen data and do not suffer from overfitting.For both models, increasing the learning capacity -by raising the number of base filters or the number of attention heads in the ViT encoder -generally improves performance, particularly when accompanied by a higher number of output channels."
